## Chat Completion

### Basic text completion

```typescript
const response = await aiSuite.createChatCompletion(
  'openai/gpt-4o',
  [{ role: 'user', content: 'Hello!' }],
);

if (response.success) {
  console.log(response.content);        // string | null
  console.log(response.usage);          // token counts
  console.log(response.execution_time); // milliseconds
} else {
  console.error(response.error);        // string
  console.error(response.tag);          // error category
}
```

### Messages format

```typescript
type MessageModel =
  | { role: 'user' | 'developer'; content: string | ContentPart | ContentPart[]; name?: string }
  | { role: 'assistant'; content: string | ContentPart | ContentPart[]; name?: string }
  | { role: 'tool'; content: string | ContentPart | ContentPart[]; name?: string }

// Content parts
type ContentPart =
  | { type: 'text'; text: string }
  | { type: 'image'; image: string | Buffer }
  | { type: 'file'; mediaType: 'application/pdf' | 'image/png' | 'image/jpg' | 'image/jpeg' | 'image/gif' | 'image/webp'; file: Buffer | ArrayBuffer | string; fileName: string }
```

- `user`: human message
- `developer`: system/instruction message (mapped per provider)
- `assistant`: model response
- `tool`: tool call result

### Response format — JSON Schema (structured output with Zod)

```typescript
import { z } from 'zod';

const schema = z.object({
  name: z.string(),
  age: z.number(),
  email: z.string().email(),
});

const response = await aiSuite.createChatCompletion(
  'openai/gpt-4o',
  [{ role: 'user', content: 'Generate a sample user profile' }],
  {
    responseFormat: 'json_schema',
    zodSchema: schema,
  },
);

if (response.success) {
  console.log(response.content_object); // typed, validated object
}
```

### Response format — JSON Object

```typescript
const response = await aiSuite.createChatCompletion(
  'anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6',
  [{ role: 'user', content: 'Return a JSON with key "result"' }],
  { responseFormat: 'json_object' },
);

if (response.success) {
  console.log(response.content_object); // parsed Record<string, unknown>
}
```

### Temperature, max tokens

```typescript
const response = await aiSuite.createChatCompletion(
  'gemini/gemini-2.5-flash',
  messages,
  {
    responseFormat: 'text',
    temperature: 0.2,
    maxOutputTokens: 1024,
  },
);
```

### Tool calling (function calling)

```typescript
const response = await aiSuite.createChatCompletion(
  'openai/gpt-4o',
  [{ role: 'user', content: 'What is the weather in Tokyo?' }],
  {
    responseFormat: 'text',
    tools: [
      {
        type: 'function',
        function: {
          name: 'get_weather',
          description: 'Get the current weather for a location',
          parameters: {
            type: 'object',
            properties: {
              location: { type: 'string', description: 'City name' },
            },
            required: ['location'],
            additionalProperties: false,
          },
          additionalProperties: false,
          strict: true,
        },
      },
    ],
  },
);

if (response.success && response.tools) {
  for (const tool of response.tools) {
    console.log(tool.name);    // function name
    console.log(tool.content); // parsed arguments as object
  }
}
```

### Reasoning mode (OpenAI o1/o3, Grok)

```typescript
const response = await aiSuite.createChatCompletion(
  'openai/o3',
  [{ role: 'user', content: 'Prove the Pythagorean theorem.' }],
  {
    responseFormat: 'text',
    reasoning: { effort: 'high' }, // 'low' | 'medium' | 'high'
  },
);

if (response.success) {
  console.log(response.usage?.reasoning_tokens);
}
```

### Thinking mode (Gemini 2.5)

```typescript
const response = await aiSuite.createChatCompletion(
  'gemini/gemini-2.5-pro',
  messages,
  {
    responseFormat: 'text',
    thinking: {
      budget: 512,   // thinking budget tokens
      output: true,  // include thinking in output
    },
  },
);

if (response.success) {
  console.log(response.usage?.thoughts_tokens);
}
```

### Multi-provider parallel completion

```typescript
const results = await aiSuite.createChatCompletionMultiResult(
  ['openai/gpt-4o', 'anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6', 'gemini/gemini-2.5-flash'],
  [{ role: 'user', content: 'Summarize quantum computing in one sentence.' }],
);

// results is an array in the same order as the providers array
for (const result of results) {
  if (result.success) console.log(result.model, result.content);
  else console.error(result.model, result.error);
}
```

### Retry logic

```typescript
const response = await aiSuite.createChatCompletion(
  'openai/gpt-4o',
  messages,
  {
    responseFormat: 'text',
    retry: {
      attempts: 3,
      delay: (attempt) => Math.pow(2, attempt) * 1000, // exponential backoff
    },
  },
);
```

