## File Upload

Supported providers: OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini.

Files are typically .jsonl format for batch inputs. The library validates each line is valid JSON.

### Upload a file

```typescript
import { readFileSync } from 'fs';

const jsonl = readFileSync('./data.jsonl');
const file = new File([jsonl], 'data.jsonl', { type: 'text/jsonl' });

const result = await aiSuite.file.create('openai', file, {
  retry: {
    attempts: 3,
    delay: (attempt) => attempt * 1000,
  },
});

if (result.success) {
  console.log('File ID:', result.content.id);
  console.log('Size:', result.content.bytes);
}
```

### List files

```typescript
const result = await aiSuite.file.list('openai', { limit: 20 });
if (result.success) {
  for (const f of result.content) {
    console.log(f.id, f.filename, f.bytes);
  }
}
```

### Retrieve file metadata

```typescript
const result = await aiSuite.file.retrieve('openai', 'file-id-123', {});
if (result.success) {
  console.log(result.content); // { id, filename, bytes, created_at, expires_at }
}
```

### Delete a file

```typescript
const result = await aiSuite.file.delete('openai', 'file-id-123', {});
```

